  "screens": [
    {
      "focus_terms": [
        "bayes_theorem"
      ],
      "id": "s019",
      "introduced_terms": [
        "bayes_theorem"
      ],
      "lines": [
        "现在换一种思路：用概率来做分类。",
        "这就是 <term id=\"bayes_theorem\">贝叶斯定理</term> 的用武之地。"
      ],
      "type": "narration"
    },
    {
      "focus_terms": [],
      "id": "s020",
      "introduced_terms": [],
      "lines": [
        "想象一下：你看到一个又红又圆的物体。",
        "它有多大概率是一个苹果？"
      ],
      "type": "narration"
    },
    {
      "focus_terms": [],
      "id": "s021",
      "introduced_terms": [],
      "lines": [
        "我们用 H 表示“它是苹果”这个假设，",
        "用 X 表示“它是红且圆的”这个观察。"
      ],
      "type": "narration"
    },
    {
      "focus_terms": [
        "posterior_probability"
      ],
      "id": "s022",
      "introduced_terms": [
        "posterior_probability"
      ],
      "lines": [
        "我们想求的是 P(H|X)，也就是 <term id=\"posterior_probability\">后验概率</term>。",
        "即：看到 X 之后，H 为真的概率。"
      ],
      "type": "narration"
    },
    {
      "focus_terms": [],
      "id": "s023",
      "introduced_terms": [],
      "lines": [
        "贝叶斯定理告诉我们：",
        "P(H|X) = P(X|H) * P(H) / P(X)"
      ],
      "type": "narration"
    },
    {
      "focus_terms": [
        "prior_probability",
        "likelihood"
      ],
      "id": "s024",
      "introduced_terms": [
        "prior_probability",
        "likelihood"
      ],
      "lines": [
        "P(H) 是 <term id=\"prior_probability\">先验概率</term>：随便拿个东西，它是苹果的概率。",
        "P(X|H) 是 <term id=\"likelihood\">似然</term>：如果它是苹果，它是红且圆的概率。"
      ],
      "type": "narration"
    },
    {
      "focus_terms": [],
      "id": "s025",
      "introduced_terms": [],
      "lines": [
        "应用到分类上：对于每个可能的类别 Cᵢ，",
        "我们计算 P(Cᵢ|X)，然后选最大的那个。"
      ],
      "type": "narration"
    },
    {
      "focus_terms": [],
      "id": "s026",
      "introduced_terms": [],
      "lines": [
        "但直接计算 P(X|Cᵢ) 非常困难，",
        "因为 X 包含多个属性，组合情况太多。"
      ],
      "type": "narration"
    },
    {
      "focus_terms": [
        "naive_bayes"
      ],
      "id": "s027",
      "introduced_terms": [
        "conditional_independence",
        "naive_bayes"
      ],
      "lines": [
        "于是有了一个大胆的假设：<term id=\"conditional_independence\">条件独立</term>。",
        "也就是 <term id=\"naive_bayes\">朴素贝叶斯</term> 的核心。"
      ],
      "type": "narration"
    },
    {
      "focus_terms": [],
      "id": "s028",
      "introduced_terms": [],
      "lines": [
        "它假设：在给定类别的情况下，所有属性之间相互独立。",
        "也就是说，知道“年龄”不会影响你对“收入”的判断。"
      ],
      "type": "narration"
    },
    {
      "focus_terms": [],
      "formula": {
        "latex": "P(X|C_i) = \\prod_{k=1}^{m} P(x_k|C_i)",
        "spoken": "给定类别 Cᵢ 时，观察到 X 的概率等于每个属性值概率的乘积。"
      },
      "id": "s029",
      "introduced_terms": [],
      "lines": [
        "这样，P(X|Cᵢ) 就可以分解为所有属性概率的乘积："
      ],
      "type": "formula"
    },
    {
      "exercise": {
        "answer": 0,
        "explanation": "朴素贝叶斯假设在给定类别的情况下，所有属性条件独立。",
